Actress Uche Jombo has called for the imprisonment of husband of late popular gospel singer Osinachi Nwachukwu. The deceased, who was a lead singer at the Dunamis International Headquarters, Abuja died on April 8, after being in a coma for five days following alleged assault by her husband. Colleagues, family members and children of Osinachi confirmed the allegations, accusing Peter Nwachukwu of domestic violence and maltreatment. Nwachukwu, who was immediately arrested by the police after the younger brother of the deceased singer reported the matter, leading to an investigation denied the domestic violence allegations levelled against him.   Ugandan filmmaker eyes new Africa narrative after Disney…     Why I flaunt my pregnancy – Rihanna     DJ Cuppy pledges to sponsor lady’s varsity education   But Uche Jombo, in her reaction to death of the gospel singer known for her collaborative hit track ‘Ekwueme’, noted Peter Nwachukwu was the greatest enemy of his late wife. The film star further anticipated a long jail term for accused which according to her will be due justice for the deceased singer. “The more I read and hear the sadder her death becomes. Osinachi’s story keep getting worse; how can a man do this to someone he was supposed to love and protect? “I hope he will be locked up for life. She deserves justice! He was her greatest life enemy in disguise, ” she tweeted.